  "section_anchors": [
    {
      "text": "We address this gap and present OccAny, the first unconstrained urban 3D occupancy model capable of operating on out-of-domain uncalibrated scenes",
      "expected_section": "Abstract",
      "position": "middle"
    },
    {
      "text": "We propose the first generalized 3D occupancy framework",
      "expected_section": "Abstract",
      "position": "middle"
    },
    {
      "text": "A key task in this area is 3D occupancy prediction whose goal is to infer a voxelized map of the environment",
      "expected_section": "Introduction",
      "position": "middle"
    },
    {
      "text": "We introduce a novel pipeline for urban 3D occupancy prediction that emphasizes scalability and generalization.",
      "expected_section": "Introduction",
      "position": "middle"
    },
    {
      "text": "Visual geometry foundation model. Dust3r [66] introduced the visual geometry foundation model, which uses large-scale pointmap prediction to solve diverse 3D tasks.",
      "expected_section": "Related works",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "We build OccAny, a 3D occupancy framework that can generalize to arbitrary out-of-domain urban scenes.",
      "expected_section": "Method",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "The 3D Reconstruction stage aims to recover the scene geometry from a set of reconstruction frames",
      "expected_section": "3D Reconstruction with Segmentation Forcing",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "The Segmentation Forcing loss compels OccAny to predict SAM2-like features.",
      "expected_section": "3D Reconstruction with Segmentation Forcing",
      "position": "middle"
    },
    {
      "text": "We train a rendering encoder Ee and decoder De to predict pointmaps and SAM2-like features for arbitrary novel views",
      "expected_section": "Novel-View Rendering",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "We first retrieve the reconstructed pointmaps, SAM2-like features and the registered camera poses of all Nrec input frames from the 3D Reconstruction stage.",
      "expected_section": "OccAny Inference",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "Both stages are trained using the same set of losses",
      "expected_section": "Training Losses",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "We evaluate the generalization of OccAny on two out-of-domain benchmarks: SemanticKITTI [1] and Occ3D-NuScenes [59]",
      "expected_section": "Experiments",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "We first quantitatively evaluate our method using synthetic data with ground-truth surface details.",
      "expected_section": "Main results",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tab. 6 analyzes the contribution of each proposed component.",
      "expected_section": "Analysis",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "We propose for the first time a generalized 3D occupancy network, called OccAny, that is trained once and perform zero-shot inference on arbitrary out-of-domain sequential, monocular and surround-view unposed data.",
      "expected_section": "Conclusion",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "Occ3D-NuScenes was built upon nuScenes [4].",
      "expected_section": "Datasets",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "The 3D Reconstruction stage (cf . Sec. 3.1) is trained in two consecutive steps:",
      "expected_section": "Training",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "For the 3D Reconstruction phase, we substitute the reconstruction encoder E and decoder D from MUSt3R with DA3 backbone",
      "expected_section": "OccAny+ using DA3 and SAM3",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "We present here the supplementary studies not presented in the main text due to the lack of space.",
      "expected_section": "Supplementary Studies",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "While the unified OccAny model conveniently uses distilled segmentation features, it can also be combined with the original features from segmentation foundation models at inference.",
      "expected_section": "Boosting semantic performance",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tab. 8 details results and method constraints in the surround-view setting",
      "expected_section": "More surround-view results",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "In this experiment, we compare the effectiveness of our Novel-View Rendering stage (cf . Sec. 3.2) with a baseline that performs depth completion on the projected pointmaps of the novel views.",
      "expected_section": "Novel-View Rendering vs. Depth Completion",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "We assess the generalization capability of SOTA 3D fully-supervised models by evaluating models trained on a source dataset directly on a different target dataset.",
      "expected_section": "Generalization of State-of-the-art (SOTA) 3D Supervised Occupancy Models",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "We assess the quality of ego-trajectory prediction using OccAny on the nuScenes validation set",
      "expected_section": "Ego Vehicle Trajectory Prediction",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "We report in Tab. 12 the memory consumption and running time of NVR inference using one A100 GPU in the surround-view setting.",
      "expected_section": "NVR complexity",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "We are report the model sizes and speeds of OccAny and baselines in Tab. 13.",
      "expected_section": "Model sizes and speeds",
      "position": "start"
    },
    {
      "text": "We show additional qualitative results in Fig. 9, Fig. 10, Fig. 11, Fig. 12, and Fig. 13.",
      "expected_section": "Qualitative Examples",
      "position": "start"
    }
  ],
